# Web client (from PROJECT_GUIDELINES.md)

## Tests before implementation

For **each new or substantially changed UI component:** write **tests first** (React Testing Library + Vitest/Jest), then implement. Test **behaviour** (render, interaction, a11y), not implementation details.

## Redux (RTK)

- `@reduxjs/toolkit` + `react-redux`. Typed **`useAppDispatch`** / **`useAppSelector`** from one module (e.g. `store/hooks.ts`).
- Feature **`createSlice`**; middleware for logging, analytics, API error normalization as needed.
- **Custom hooks** in `hooks/` wrapping selectors + dispatch + router. **Local state** for UI-only (modals, fields); do not put every keystroke in Redux.
- Unit-test non-trivial slice logic and hooks.

## UI quality

- Pixel-conscious, calm theme (colour, contrast, spacing, typography). Smooth scroll/section motion where specified without harming focus.
- **Accessibility:** keyboard, visible focus, no traps, semantic HTML, ARIA when needed.
- **One primary component per file.** Non-prop types in module **`types.ts`**; props types may stay with the component.

## Tooling

- Each app has **its own** ESLint/Prettier/TS config (`TASK_CHECKLIST.md`); no monorepo-root config for all apps.
